text: The Finnish War (, , ) was a war fought in 1808-1809 between Russia and Sweden. King Gustav IV Adolf of Sweden lost, and Sweden lost its Eastern third. The lost land became the autonomous Grand Duchy of Finland. == References == ==Other websites== Category:1808 Category:1809 Category:History of Finland Category:Wars involving Russia Category:19th century in Sweden Category:19th-century conflicts
